        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/28/6" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2008.28.issue-6/asset/14a1685b-fc14-1685-7fc1-a1685b7fc14a/radiographics.2008.28.issue-6.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">28</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">6</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Oct 1 2008</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1571</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1590</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18936022/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18936022</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2008.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Oct 1 2008</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.286075141">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IVC+%3D+inferior+vena+cava&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IVC = inferior vena cava</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPR+%3D+multiplanar+reformatted&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPR = multiplanar reformatted</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The relevant retroperitoneal anatomy, imaging technique in the evaluation of traumatic retroperitoneal injuries, injuries to retroperitoneal structures, abnormal posttraumatic findings within the retroperitoneum, and a proposed algorithm for the diagnosis of these injuries are discussed and illustrated.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Kevin P.</span> <span property="familyName">Daly</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Virginia Health System, Charlottesville, Va. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2006 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received June 21, 2007; revision requested December 11; final revision received April 1, 2008; accepted April 2. S.B.G. is on the advisory board of Onex (Carestream Health) and with the speakers’ bureau of GE Healthcare; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Daly/Kevin+P" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Christopher P.</span> <span property="familyName">Ho</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Virginia Health System, Charlottesville, Va. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2006 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received June 21, 2007; revision requested December 11; final revision received April 1, 2008; accepted April 2. S.B.G. is on the advisory board of Onex (Carestream Health) and with the speakers’ bureau of GE Healthcare; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class=